Just now, si2504 said:

I only wanted the Runway statics mainly...

You could "harvest them" This involves the following;

  • Install the mode as normal
  • delete the directory \KerbinSideRemastered\Statics\ExampleBases to remove all bases
  • delete the file \KerbinSideRemastered\MiniAVC.dll
  • Never Update the mod after doing this.

Then you will have access the the statics that make up the runways and taxiways and should be able to use then in your bases.  But test and if it causes issues, if so, remove the mod completely.

I've done this with a number of older Kerbal Konstruct mods to access their parts for private use and it mostly works. 

Anything you build with these parts that you might want to distribute to others must carry the original grant of License for this mod.

1 hour ago, Ben J. Kerman said:

Kerbinside work with KSP 1.12

Kerbin Side Remastered works in KSP 1.12.1. The original Kerbin Side is more problematic, and likely does not.

In version 1.12.1, the context menu of Kerbin Кonstruction does not work. Therefore, you cannot change the position of objects, add new ones, and so on. Kerbin Side Remasterеd and original Kerbin Side, Kosmodrome, Kerbin City and others are working. At least on my installation.

@Sokol_323 Yes. the CTL-K edit feature of Kerbal Konstructs does not work in 1.12.1. However the function of the KK static facilities that make up Kerbin Side Remastered work as intended. 

I keep a KSP 1.11.2 instance installed and I make all of my KK edits there and copy the updated instances to my KSP 1.12.1 active game as required.
